\begin_layout Subsection*
Part (c)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The reason that firms can get positive profits in equilibrium is because
 cost functions are convex.
 If firm 1 undercuts firm 2, firm 1's benefit is selling to the entire market.
 However, this increase in market share has a trade-off: namely that since
 marginal costs are increasing, the increased total cost may offset the
 increase in revenue from selling to the entire market.
 
\end_layout

